      "Cyclical Semiconductor Equipment Risks": [
        "Demand for ASML systems is tied to the semiconductor equipment cycle, which has historically shown 18-24 month peak-to-trough swings.",
        "Customer concentration: top 5 customers (TSMC, Samsung, Intel, SK Hynix, Micron) drive ~80% of revenue.",
        "Order delays and push-outs can compress quarterly results without affecting long-term TAM.",
        "Source: ASML 20-F Item 3.D Risk Factors."
      ],
      "Geopolitical / Export Control Risks": [
        "US-led export controls on EUV equipment to China limit ASML's TAM in the world's largest semi market.",
        "Dutch and EU export licensing requirements introduce uncertainty into deal closures.",
        "Trade tension flare-ups can trigger order cancellations or push-outs.",
        "Source: ASML 20-F Item 3.D + ongoing 6-K updates."
      ],
      "Technology Execution Risks": [
        "High-NA EUV (NXE:3800/3850) requires successful customer adoption \u2014 single-source dependence on Carl Zeiss for optics.",
        "DUV system ASP/mix shifts could pressure gross margin if customer demand skews toward older nodes.",
        "Service/upgrade revenue depends on installed-base utilization rates.",
        "Source: ASML 20-F Item 3.D."
      ],
      "FX / Currency Risks": [
        "ASML reports in EUR but ~50% of revenue is denominated in or hedged to USD.",
        "EUR/USD volatility creates translation impacts on reported financials.",
        "Currency hedging program reduces but does not eliminate FX exposure.",
        "Source: ASML 20-F Item 11."
      ],
      "Valuation & Multiple Compression Risk": [
        "P/E FY1 ~32\u00d7 and EV/EBITDA FY1 ~25\u00d7 sit above peer median.",
        "AI-driven semi equipment demand has stretched multiples \u2014 any cyclical slowdown could trigger 20-30% multiple compression.",
        "Drawdown sensitivity: 1% revenue miss historically triggers 5-10% stock move on print.",
        "Source: Implied from valuation panel."
      ]
    },
